{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"One of my favorite cartoon characters is Snoopy."},{"time":6000,"text":"I love the way he sits and lies on his kennel and contemplates the great things of life."},{"time":13000,"text":"So when I thought about compassion,"},{"time":15000,"text":"my mind immediately went to one of the cartoon strips,"},{"time":19000,"text":"where he's lying there and he says,"},{"time":23000,"text":"\"I really understand, and I really appreciate"},{"time":26000,"text":"how one should love one's neighbor as one love's oneself."},{"time":31000,"text":"The only trouble is the people next door; I can't stand them.\""},{"time":36000,"text":"This, in a way, is one of the challenges"},{"time":41000,"text":"of how to interpret a really good idea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45000,"text":"We all, I think, believe in compassion."},{"time":48000,"text":"If you look at all the world religions, all the main world religions,"},{"time":52000,"text":"you'll find within them some teaching concerning compassion."},{"time":57000,"text":"So in Judaism, we have, from our Torah,"},{"time":60000,"text":"that you should love your neighbor as you love yourself."},{"time":64000,"text":"And within Jewish teachings, the rabbinic teachings, we have Hillel,"},{"time":69000,"text":"who taught that you shouldn't do to others what you don't like being done to yourself."},{"time":74000,"text":"And all the main religions have similar teachings."},{"time":79000,"text":"And again, within Judaism,"},{"time":81000,"text":"we have a teaching about God,"},{"time":84000,"text":"who is called the compassionate one, Ha-rachaman."},{"time":87000,"text":"After all, how could the world exist without God being compassionate?"},{"time":92000,"text":"And we, as taught within the Torah that we are made in the image of God,"},{"time":97000,"text":"so we too have to be compassionate."},{"time":101000,"text":"But what does it mean? How does it impact on our everyday life?"},{"time":105000,"text":"Sometimes, of course, being compassionate"},{"time":109000,"text":"can produce feelings within us that are very difficult to control."}]},{"cues":[{"time":116000,"text":"I know there are many times when I've gone and conducted a funeral,"},{"time":122000,"text":"or when I have been sitting with the bereaved, or with people who are dying,"},{"time":128000,"text":"and I am overwhelmed by the sadness, by the difficulty,"},{"time":137000,"text":"the challenge that is there for the family, for the person."},{"time":141000,"text":"And I'm touched, so that tears come to my eyes."},{"time":146000,"text":"And yet, if I just allowed myself to be overwhelmed by these feelings,"},{"time":151000,"text":"I wouldn't be doing my job --"},{"time":154000,"text":"because I have to actually be there for them"},{"time":156000,"text":"and make sure that rituals happen, that practicalities are seen to."},{"time":164000,"text":"And yet, on the other hand, if I didn't feel this compassion,"},{"time":169000,"text":"then I feel that it would be time for me to hang up my robe"},{"time":174000,"text":"and give up being a rabbi."}]},{"cues":[{"time":177000,"text":"And these same feelings are there for all of us as we face the world."},{"time":182000,"text":"Who cannot be touched by compassion"},{"time":186000,"text":"when we see the terrible horrors of the results of war,"},{"time":193000,"text":"or famine, or earthquakes, or tsunamis?"},{"time":198000,"text":"I know some people who say"},{"time":200000,"text":"\"Well, you know there's just so much out there -- I can't do anything,"},{"time":204000,"text":"I'm not going to even begin to try.\""},{"time":208000,"text":"And there are some charity workers who call this compassion fatigue."},{"time":214000,"text":"There are others who feel they can't confront compassion anymore,"},{"time":221000,"text":"and so they turn off the television and don't watch."},{"time":226000,"text":"In Judaism, though, we tend to always say, there has to be a middle way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":233000,"text":"You have to, of course, be aware of the needs of others,"},{"time":240000,"text":"but you have to be aware in such a way that you can carry on with your life"},{"time":245000,"text":"and be of help to people."},{"time":248000,"text":"So part of compassion has to be an understanding of what makes people tick."},{"time":257000,"text":"And, of course, you can't do that unless you understand yourself a bit more."}]},{"cues":[{"time":260000,"text":"And there's a lovely rabbinic interpretation of the beginnings of creation,"},{"time":267000,"text":"which says that when God created the world,"},{"time":271000,"text":"God thought that it would be best to create the world"},{"time":277000,"text":"only with the divine attribute of justice."},{"time":281000,"text":"Because, after all, God is just."},{"time":283000,"text":"Therefore, there should be justice throughout the world."},{"time":288000,"text":"And then God looked to the future and realized,"},{"time":290000,"text":"if the world was created just with justice, the world couldn't exist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":295000,"text":"So, God thought, \"Nope, I'm going to create the world just with compassion.\""},{"time":301000,"text":"And then God looked to the future and realized that,"},{"time":305000,"text":"in fact, if the world were just filled with compassion,"},{"time":309000,"text":"there would be anarchy and chaos."},{"time":313000,"text":"There had to be limits to all things."},{"time":316000,"text":"The rabbis describe this as being like a king"},{"time":321000,"text":"who has a beautiful, fragile glass bowl."},{"time":327000,"text":"If you put too much cold water in, it will shatter."},{"time":331000,"text":"If you put boiling water in, it will shatter."},{"time":333000,"text":"What do you have to do? Put in a mixture of the two."},{"time":338000,"text":"And so God put both of these possibilities into the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":346000,"text":"There is something more though that has to be there."},{"time":350000,"text":"And that is the translation of the feelings"},{"time":355000,"text":"that we may have about compassion"},{"time":358000,"text":"into the wider world, into action."},{"time":362000,"text":"So, like Snoopy, we can't just lie there"},{"time":365000,"text":"and think great thoughts about our neighbors."},{"time":368000,"text":"We actually have to do something about it."},{"time":371000,"text":"And so there is also, within Judaism, this notion of love and kindness"},{"time":376000,"text":"that becomes very important: \"chesed.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":381000,"text":"All these three things, then, have to be melded together."},{"time":386000,"text":"The idea of justice, which gives boundaries to our lives"},{"time":392000,"text":"and gives us a feeling of what's right about life, what's right about living,"},{"time":399000,"text":"what should we be doing, social justice."},{"time":403000,"text":"There has to be a willingness to do good deeds,"},{"time":408000,"text":"but not, of course, at the expense of our own sanity."},{"time":412000,"text":"You know, there's no way that you can do anything for anyone"},{"time":415000,"text":"if you overdo things."},{"time":417000,"text":"And balancing them all in the middle is this notion of compassion,"},{"time":423000,"text":"which has to be there, if you like, at our very roots."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429000,"text":"This idea of compassion comes to us"},{"time":434000,"text":"because we're made in the image of God,"},{"time":437000,"text":"who is ultimately the compassionate one."},{"time":441000,"text":"What does this compassion entail?"},{"time":443000,"text":"It entails understanding the pain of the other."},{"time":448000,"text":"But even more than that,"},{"time":450000,"text":"it means understanding one's connection to the whole of creation:"},{"time":458000,"text":"understanding that one is part of that creation,"},{"time":462000,"text":"that there is a unity that underlies all that we see,"},{"time":466000,"text":"all that we hear, all that we feel."},{"time":470000,"text":"I call that unity God."},{"time":473000,"text":"And that unity is something that connects all of creation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":478000,"text":"And, of course, in the modern world, with the environmental movement,"},{"time":481000,"text":"we're becoming even more aware of the connectivity of things,"},{"time":486000,"text":"that something I do here actually does matter in Africa,"},{"time":491000,"text":"that if I use too much of my carbon allowance,"},{"time":495000,"text":"it seems to be that we are causing"},{"time":497000,"text":"a great lack of rain in central and eastern Africa."},{"time":504000,"text":"So there is a connectivity,"},{"time":506000,"text":"and I have to understand that -- as part of the creation,"},{"time":512000,"text":"as part of me being made in the image of God."},{"time":517000,"text":"And I have to understand that my needs"},{"time":521000,"text":"sometimes have to be sublimated to other needs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":525000,"text":"This \"18 minutes\" business, I find quite fascinating."},{"time":530000,"text":"Because in Judaism, the number 18, in Hebrew letters,"},{"time":535000,"text":"stands for life -- the word \"life.\""},{"time":538000,"text":"So, in a sense, the 18 minutes is challenging me to say,"},{"time":543000,"text":"\"In life, this is what's important in terms of compassion.\""},{"time":547000,"text":"But, something else as well:"},{"time":549000,"text":"actually, 18 minutes is important."},{"time":552000,"text":"Because at Passover, when we have to eat unleavened bread,"},{"time":558000,"text":"the rabbis say, what is the difference between dough that is made into bread,"},{"time":562000,"text":"and dough that is made into unleavened bread, or \"matzah\"?"},{"time":565000,"text":"And they say \"It's 18 minutes.\""},{"time":568000,"text":"Because that's how long they say it takes for this dough to become leaven."},{"time":573000,"text":"What does it mean, \"dough becomes leaven\"?"},{"time":576000,"text":"It means it gets filled with hot air."},{"time":579000,"text":"What's matzah? What's unleavened bread? You don't get it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":583000,"text":"Symbolically, what the rabbis say is that at Passover,"},{"time":588000,"text":"what we have to do is try to get rid of our hot air -- our pride,"},{"time":594000,"text":"our feeling that we are the most important people in the whole entire world,"},{"time":598000,"text":"and that everything should revolve round us."},{"time":602000,"text":"So we try and get rid of those,"},{"time":605000,"text":"and so doing, try to get rid of the habits, the emotions, the ideas"},{"time":612000,"text":"that enslave us, that make our eyes closed, give us tunnel vision"},{"time":618000,"text":"so we don't see the needs of others --"},{"time":621000,"text":"and free ourselves and free ourselves from that."},{"time":625000,"text":"And that too is a basis for having compassion,"},{"time":630000,"text":"for understanding our place in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":636000,"text":"Now there is, in Judaism, a gorgeous story"},{"time":641000,"text":"of a rich man who sat in synagogue one day."},{"time":647000,"text":"And, as many people do, he was dozing off during the sermon."},{"time":653000,"text":"And as he was dozing off, they were reading from the book of Leviticus in the Torah."},{"time":659000,"text":"And they were saying that in the ancient times in the temple in Jerusalem,"},{"time":665000,"text":"the priests used to have bread,"},{"time":667000,"text":"which they used to place into a special table in the temple in Jerusalem."},{"time":675000,"text":"The man was asleep, but he heard the words bread, temple, God, and he woke up."},{"time":682000,"text":"He said, \"God wants bread. That's it. God wants bread. I know what God wants.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":687000,"text":"And he rushed home. And after the Sabbath, he made 12 loaves of bread,"},{"time":694000,"text":"took them to the synagogue, went into the synagogue,"},{"time":697000,"text":"opened the ark and said, \"God, I don't know why you want this bread, but here you are.\""},{"time":701000,"text":"And he put it in the ark with the scrolls of the Torah."},{"time":706000,"text":"Then he went home."}]},{"cues":[{"time":709000,"text":"The cleaner came into the synagogue."},{"time":712000,"text":"\"Oh God, I'm in such trouble. I've got children to feed."},{"time":716000,"text":"My wife's ill. I've got no money. What can I do?\""},{"time":720000,"text":"He goes into the synagogue. \"God, will you please help me?"},{"time":724000,"text":"Ah, what a wonderful smell.\""},{"time":726000,"text":"He goes to the ark. He opens the ark."},{"time":728000,"text":"\"There's bread! God, you've answered my plea. You've answered my question.\""},{"time":733000,"text":"Takes the bread and goes home."}]},{"cues":[{"time":736000,"text":"Meanwhile, the rich man thinks to himself,"},{"time":739000,"text":"\"I'm an idiot. God wants bread?"},{"time":742000,"text":"God, the one who rules the entire universe, wants my bread?\""},{"time":747000,"text":"He rushes to the synagogue. \"I'll get it out of the ark before anybody finds it.\""},{"time":750000,"text":"He goes in there, and it's not there."},{"time":753000,"text":"And he says, \"God, you really did want it. You wanted my bread."},{"time":758000,"text":"Next week, with raisins.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":761000,"text":"This went on for years."},{"time":763000,"text":"Every week, the man would bring bread with raisins,"},{"time":766000,"text":"with all sorts of good things, put it into the ark."},{"time":769000,"text":"Every week, the cleaner would come. \"God you've answered my plea again.\""},{"time":773000,"text":"Take the bread. Take it home."}]},{"cues":[{"time":775000,"text":"Went on until a new rabbi came. Rabbis always spoil things."},{"time":778000,"text":"The rabbi came in and saw what was going on."},{"time":783000,"text":"And he called the two of them to his office."},{"time":785000,"text":"And he said, you know, \"This is what's happening.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":788000,"text":"And the rich man -- oh, dear -- crestfallen."},{"time":794000,"text":"\"You mean God didn't want my bread?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":798000,"text":"And the poor man said, \"And you mean God didn't answer my pleas?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":805000,"text":"And the rabbi said, \"You've misunderstood me."},{"time":809000,"text":"You've misunderstood totally,\" he said."},{"time":812000,"text":"\"Of course, what you are doing,\" he said to the rich man,"},{"time":816000,"text":"\"is answering God's plea that we should be compassionate."},{"time":822000,"text":"And God,\" he said to the poor man, \"is answering your plea"},{"time":826000,"text":"that people should be compassionate and give.\""},{"time":830000,"text":"He looked at the rich man. He held the rich man's hands and said,"},{"time":836000,"text":"\"Don't you understand?\" He said, \"These are the hands of God.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":847000,"text":"So that is the way I feel:"},{"time":853000,"text":"that I can only try to approach this notion of being compassionate,"},{"time":860000,"text":"of understanding that there is a connectivity, that there is a unity in this world;"},{"time":866000,"text":"that I want to try and serve that unity,"},{"time":871000,"text":"and that I can try and do that by understanding, I hope,"},{"time":875000,"text":"trying to understand something of the pain of others;"},{"time":880000,"text":"but understanding that there are limits, that people have to bear responsibility"},{"time":883000,"text":"for some of the problems that come upon them;"},{"time":888000,"text":"and that I have to understand that there are limits to my energy,"},{"time":891000,"text":"to the giving I can give."},{"time":894000,"text":"I have to reevaluate them,"},{"time":897000,"text":"try and separate out the material things"},{"time":902000,"text":"and my emotions that may be enslaving me,"},{"time":906000,"text":"so that I can see the world clearly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":910000,"text":"And then I have to try to see in what ways"},{"time":915000,"text":"I can make these the hands of God."},{"time":920000,"text":"And so try to bring compassion to life in this world."}]}]}